  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nOne of the features mentioned in #95 is to store the validator preferences (preferred fee recipient and gas limit for a given validator) and then send them at a regular interval to the relays.\r\n\r\nAs there are many ways to implement this feature, I think it could be interesting to have a discussion about which one is the best.\r\n\r\n## 1 : Use a separate goroutine\r\n\r\nWe can have a goroutine which reads the registered preferences in a safe map and sends those values to the relays at a regular interval, something like :\r\n\r\n```golang\r\n\r\n// BoostService TODO\r\ntype BoostService struct {\r\n\t// Backend stuff...\r\n\r\n\t// The validators preferred fee recipient and gas limit\r\n\tmu          sync.RWMutex\r\n\tpreferences map[string]types.SignedValidatorRegistration\r\n}\r\n\r\n// sendValidatorPreferencesAtInterval is launched as a goroutine\r\nfunc (m *BoostService) sendValidatorPreferencesAtInterval(done chan bool) {\r\n\tticker := time.NewTicker(time.Minute)\r\n\tdefer ticker.Stop()\r\n\r\n\tfor {\r\n\t\tselect {\r\n\t\tcase <-done:\r\n\t\t\treturn\r\n\r\n\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\r\n\t\t\t// Loads preferences from map after declaration\r\n\t\t\tpayload := []types.SignedValidatorRegistration{}\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t// Send to each relay\r\n\t\t\tfor _, relay := range m.relays {\r\n\t\t\t\terr := SendHTTPRequest(context.Background(), m.httpClient, http.MethodPost, url, payload, nil)\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc (m *BoostService) handleRegisterValidator(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request) {\r\n\t// ...\r\n\tfor _, registration := range payload {\r\n\t\t// Sanity checks...\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t// Stores the SignedValidatorRegistration and maps it to the validator's public key\r\n\t\tm.mu.Lock()\r\n\t\tm.preferences[registration.Message.Pubkey.String()] = registration\r\n\t\tm.mu.Unlock()\r\n\t}\r\n\t// ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'd like to have your opinion about this, or if you have a better solution !",
